• The ISO 5149-1:2014 standard specifies requirements relating to the safety of persons and property for the design, construction, installation, and operation of refrigerating systems. 
• For RAC systems not unitary and split-type air-conditioners installed for ‘human comfort’ in general occupancy categories, charge limitation is determined by relevant requirements indicated in the ISO 5149-1:2014 standard.
• The formula to calculate maximum charge limit as per IEC standards are presented:
  Refrigerant Charge limit = mmax = 2.5 x LFL5/4 x h0 x A1/2 
    Where: mmax : allowable maximum charge in a room in kg; 
           A : room area in m2;
           LFL : lower flammable limit in kg/m3;
           h0 : installation height of the appliance in m.
